headline: Starbucks Misses Earnings, but Stock Rises on Revenue Improvements
summary: Starbucks’  fiscal fourth-quarter earnings fell short of expectations, but the stock rose in after-hour trading Wednesday on news that the company’s same-store sales had finally turned positive.  Starbucks’ adjusted earnings of 52 cents a share came in below consensus estimates calling for 56 cents a share, according to FactSet.  Unadjusted operating margins fell 7.1 percentage points year over year, partially because of investments in more labor hours, as well as costs associated with closing coffeehouses—Starbucks shuttered 107 stores throughout the quarter.

headline: Starbucks Cafe Sales Stabilize After Year-and-a-Half-Long Slide
summary: Starbucks  said its turnaround efforts are stabilizing the world’s largest coffee chain.  The Seattle company on Wednesday reported the U.S. same-store sales for the three months ended Sept. 28 were flat, an improvement after six consecutive quarterly declines.  For its fourth quarter, Starbucks reported earnings adjusted for one-time items of 52 cents a share, missing the 56-cent estimate from analysts polled by FactSet.

headline: Starbucks sales improve but store closures and layoffs take a bite out of profits
summary: Starbucks reported better-than-expected revenue in its fiscal fourth quarter as its U.S. sales improved. Starbucks' global same-store sales, or sales at locations open at least a year, rose 1% compared to the same period a year ago.
